      "writtenOn": "2020-12-01T02:47:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:appengine/cr-buildbucket/api.py;l\u003d439-442\n\nThe original python code clears req.Build.Output.Properties and then call merge(): [1]\nI guess the python implementation is ok with merging the messages when\n- mask has \"build.output.properties\", but\n- req.Build.Output.Properties is None\n\n\nHowever, this causes a panic in Go.\n```\n  // clear the request fields before merge.\n  if req.Build.Output !\u003d nil {\n    req.Build.Output.Properties \u003d nil\n  }\n  buildMask.Merge(req.Build, \u0026b.Proto) # panic()\n```\n\nUnlike req.Build.Tags and req.Build.Steps, req.Build.Output.Properties is treated as a scalar value and merge() panics at https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/common/proto/mask/mask.go;l\u003d406\nhttps://paste.googleplex.com/6220605289398272\n\nyiwzhang@ and nodir@, is this an intended behaviour?",
